<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2778] Allow easy extension of RAMDirectory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2778</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;RAMDirectory uses RAMFiles to store the data. RAMFile offers a newBuffer() method for extensions to override and allocate buffers differently, from e.g. a pool or something. However, RAMDirectory always allocates RAMFile and doesn&apos;t allow allocating a RAMFile extension, which makes RAMFile.newBuffer() unusable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we can simply introduce a newRAMFile() method on RAMDirectory and make the RAMFiles map protected, and it will allow really extending RAMDir.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will post a patch later.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
